          "type": "text",
          "heading": "The Challenge",
          "content": "<h2>Starting Conditions<br><br></h2><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\">Mrs. Kumar's is an independent restaurant competing in a saturated local market. Before structured SEO work, the site faced the following challenges:</div><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\"><br></div><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\"><span style=\"white-space: normal;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>•<span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>Zero visibility for non-branded keywords. The site was invisible for generic local search terms like 'Indian restaurant Monroe NJ' or 'Indian food near me'.<br><br></span></div><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\"><span style=\"white-space: normal;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>•<span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>No content strategy. The blog existed but had no topical authority or keyword targeting. Posts were not driving organic traffic.<br><br></span></div><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\"><span style=\"white-space: normal;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>•<span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>Low click-through rates. Homepage CTR was 4.67% but secondary pages like the blog and catering were well below 1%.<br><br></span></div><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\"><span style=\"white-space: normal;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>•<span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>No authority backlinks. An independent restaurant site has no natural inbound link profile without active outreach or directory submissions.<br><br></span></div><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\"><span style=\"white-space: normal;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>•<span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>Technical subdomain confusion. The site operated across mrskumars.com and mobile.mrskumars.com without clear SEO consolidation, splitting ranking signals.<br><br></span></div><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\"><span style=\"white-space: normal;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>•<span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>Untapped SERP features. The site was not appearing in Knowledge Panels, Sitelinks, or Product Snippets consistently despite being a branded local business.<br><br></span></div><div bis_skin_checked=\"1\"><span style=\"white-space: normal;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>•<span style=\"white-space:pre\">\t</span>Thin location pages. Pages like /restaurant-in-princeton-junction-nj existed but had minimal SEO depth to rank for local search intent.</span></div>"
